cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use BlindSpot-Bench or its findings, please cite the paper."
title: "BlindSpot-Bench: Measuring the Oversight Gap Exactly"
authors:
  - family-names: Alami
    given-names: Daniel
year: 2026
url: "https://github.com/sparckix/blindspot-bench"
repository-code: "https://github.com/sparckix/blindspot-bench"
abstract: >-
  A research environment that makes the LLM oversight gap (the divergence between a
  channel-limited overseer's beliefs and exact ground truth) a computed number under
  optimization pressure. The gap opens as a threshold and localizes by probe stability.
  Its locus fingerprints the agent (withhold vs. fabricate), it is observable without
  ground truth, and the pattern reproduces in a second non-economy world and under a
  non-LLM optimizer. The world, the oversight protocol, and the agent model are swappable.
keywords:
  - AI safety
  - scalable oversight
  - reward hacking
  - specification gaming
  - LLM agents
  - evaluation
